<details class="gov-details halo-panel">
    <summary class="gov-details__summary">Steam client console: open and download</summary>
    <div class="gov-details__text">
        <p class="gov-body">
            The Steam client has a hidden console that accepts download commands. A community guide:
            <a target="_blank" href="https://wiki.fireundubh.com/kingdomcome/steam-console">https://wiki.fireundubh.com/kingdomcome/steam-console</a>
        </p>

        <h4 class="gov-heading-m">Open the Steam console</h4>
        <ol class="gov-steps">
            <li class="gov-body">Ensure Steam is running and you are signed in.</li>
            <li class="gov-body">
                Open the console via URI:
                <pre class="gov-pre"><code>steam://nav/console</code></pre>
                Paste that into Run/URL bar to open the Steam console.
            </li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="gov-heading-m">Run the generated command</h4>
        <ol class="gov-steps">
            <li class="gov-body">Paste each generated <code>download_depot</code> line into the console.</li>
            <li class="gov-body">Wait for completion — output may be minimal.</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="gov-heading-m">Where Steam stores downloads</h4>
        <p class="gov-body">
            Steam typically stores content under <code>steamapps/content</code> inside the Steam install folder.
        </p>

        <details class="gov-details">
            <summary class="gov-details__summary">Useful links</summary>
            <div class="gov-details__text">
                <ul class="gov-list">
                    <li class="gov-body"><a target="_blank" href="https://wiki.fireundubh.com/kingdomcome/steam-console">Community guide to Steam console</a></li>
                    <li class="gov-body"><a target="_blank" href="https://gist.github.com/r-pufky/786c26993b1c0147a1e40266c386f570">Gist: Steam parameters + console notes</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details class="gov-details">
            <summary class="gov-details__summary">Common issues</summary>
            <div class="gov-details__text">
                <ul class="gov-list">
                    <li class="gov-body">If output shows nothing, the download may still be happening — check disk activity.</li>
                    <li class="gov-body">If download fails, confirm you’re logged in and own the content.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </details>
    </div>
</details>
